  <meta name=&quot;CocoaVersion&quot; content=&quot;1265.21&quot;>
&quot;
isn&#x27;t tracking.<p>The editor is a rich text editor and allows saving formatted text in <i>.doc, </i>.html, <i>.rtf, </i>.odt, *.xml. It can&#x27;t save text unformatted so using it for raw text/HTML/XML doesn&#x27;t work.<p>&quot;So now newbies to Mac apps can&#x27;t even publish webpages,&quot; Macs come with the Apple store and you can download dozens of HTML editors for free. I search in &#x27;HTML&#x27; and the first result is the free TextWrangler.<p>Everything else you theorize is just over the top and has nothing to do with HTML editing.
